abstract: President Trump is under intense scrutiny over a classified whistle-blower complaint about some of his behavior.
snippet: President Trump is under intense scrutiny over a classified whistle-blower complaint about some of his behavior.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump is under intense scrutiny over a classified whistle-blower complaint about his behavior, which at least partly involves his dealings with Ukraine’s new president and Mr. Trump’s call for Ukraine’s government to investigate former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., who is a leading candidate for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination.

abstract: Senators Warren and Booker shone in a forum focused on the lives of L.G.B.T.Q. Americans.
snippet: Senators Warren and Booker shone in a forum focused on the lives of L.G.B.T.Q. Americans.
lead_paragraph: There was a lot of drama. Senator Cory Booker, by way of greeting, lifted one of the moderators of Friday night’s L.G.B.T.Q. Presidential Forum right off the floor in a great bear hug. Later, an audience member interrupted Senator Amy Klobuchar with what sounded like an appeal to “protect sex workers.”

abstract: Mr. Trump, intensifying a line of attack his allies have stoked for months, accused the media of covering up the former vice president’s dealings with Ukraine.
snippet: Mr. Trump, intensifying a line of attack his allies have stoked for months, accused the media of covering up the former vice president’s dealings with Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Saturday dismissed news reports that he urged the Ukrainian president to investigate former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s son as little more than a “witch hunt” and said his dealings were “perfectly fine” and routine.

headline_main: Trump Calls Reports That He Pressured Ukraine’s President a ‘Witch Hunt’
headline_print_headline: Trump Rebuffs Reports on Whistle-Blower by Retooling a Familiar Term

abstract: The controversy centers on whether President Trump manipulated foreign policy to pressure Ukraine to take action to damage Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s election bid.
snippet: The controversy centers on whether President Trump manipulated foreign policy to pressure Ukraine to take action to damage Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s election bid.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Allegations that President Trump courted foreign interference from Ukraine to hurt his leading Democratic rival, Joseph R. Biden Jr., dominated presidential politics on Saturday, as Mr. Biden demanded a House investigation of Mr. Trump’s phone call with Ukraine’s leader and as Mr. Trump lashed out, denying wrongdoing without releasing a transcript of the call.

abstract: She had a plan to take on big banks. In the fight to get it done, she honed the approach to politics that defines her presidential campaign.
snippet: She had a plan to take on big banks. In the fight to get it done, she honed the approach to politics that defines her presidential campaign.
lead_paragraph: Elizabeth Warren did not want a goodbye party. She told her aides there would be no grand send-off, no celebration of a mission accomplished.

abstract: The president and his allies have been pressing Ukraine for months to investigate Joseph R. Biden Jr., complicating relations between the two countries.
snippet: The president and his allies have been pressing Ukraine for months to investigate Joseph R. Biden Jr., complicating relations between the two countries.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For months this spring and summer, Ukraine’s newly elected president, Volodymyr Zelensky, tried to deflect pressure from President Trump and his allies to pursue investigations into former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., Mr. Biden’s son and other Trump rivals.
